https://leetcode.com/problems/01-matrix/description/


QUESTION:
Input: mat = [[0,0,0],[0,1,0],[1,1,1]]
Output: [[0,0,0],[0,1,0],[1,2,1]]

SOLUTION:
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
TIME COMPLEXITY:O(m*n)
SPACE COMPLEXITY:O(m*n)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Intuition:
  Push all 0s first, then expand like waves to fill distances for 1s.
Step 1: Identify all starting points.Collect all cells with value 0 into a queue.
Step 2: Treat all 0s as level 0 (distance = 0). Now expand outward level by level.
Step 3: Process neighbors level-wiseFor each level:
          Take all current cells from the queue.
          Look at their 4 neighbors (up, down, left, right).
          If a neighbor is 1:
          Assign it the current distance (stored as negative)Add it to the queue for the next level.
Step 4: After processing one full layer of BFS: Increase distance (dist++)
Step 5: Once a 1 is converted to a negative value:It’s no longer equal to 1. So it won’t be processed again
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
CODE:

  class Solution {
    public int[][] updateMatrix(int[][] mat) {
        Queue<int[]>q=new LinkedList<>();
        for(int i=0;i<mat.length;i++){
            for(int j=0;j<mat[0].length;j++){
                if(mat[i][j]==0){
                    q.add(new int[]{i,j});
                }
            }
        }
        int dist=1;
        int dirs[][]={{0,1},{1,0},{0,-1},{-1,0}};
        while(!q.isEmpty()){
            int size=q.size();
            for(int i=0;i<size;i++){
                int cur[]=q.poll();
                for(int dir[]:dirs){
                    int r=cur[0]+dir[0];
                    int c=cur[1]+dir[1];
                    if(r<mat.length && r>=0 && c<mat[0].length && c>=0 && mat[r][c]==1){
                        mat[r][c]=-dist;
                        q.add(new int[]{r,c});
                    } 
                    
                }
            }
            dist++;
        }
        for(int i=0;i<mat.length;i++){
            for(int j=0;j<mat[0].length;j++){
                mat[i][j]=-1*mat[i][j];
            }
        }
        return mat;
    }
}
